# Exploration 002 Summary

- Goal:
  stress-test the cash-out, progress currency, and minimum threshold for the
  best Step-009 endpoint candidate, staying estimate-level and tied to the
  inherited live far-field pressure pairing.

- What I tried:
  read the Step-009 goal, the receptionist narrowing, `step-001` far-field
  obstruction results, the Step-001 reconstruction and Tao-gate reports, the
  far-field obstruction factual notes, the obstruction-screening meta notes,
  the exact-rewrite same-protocol screening note, `CHAIN.md`, `run-006`
  chain/judgment files, and the earlier Step-009 endpoint-menu freeze report.
  I tested each candidate currency and threshold against the fixed live pairing
  `I_p^far` and against the requirement that later reconstruction and
  localization debt cannot erase the gain.

- Outcome:
  succeeded.

- One key takeaway:
  the only non-cosmetic Step-1 freeze supported by the repository is a
  full-pairing inequality on `I_p^far` whose progress currency is a genuinely
  smaller effective far-field coefficient; harmonic-moment cancellation counts
  only if it is the mechanism producing that same coefficient shrinkage.

- Recommended cash-out:
  `[VERIFIED]`
  `|I_p^far| <= C_far,eff(k) 2^{12k/5} U_k^{6/5}`
  for the same full pairing in the inherited LEI / CKN-Lin contradiction
  ledger.

- Recommended currency:
  `[VERIFIED]`
  quantified reduction of the specified nonlocal remainder, namely shrinkage of
  the effective coefficient on the live far-field pairing.

- Recommended minimum threshold:
  `[PROPOSED]`
  freeze a uniform positive-margin net shrinkage after later reconstruction and
  any required localization debt:
  `C_far,eff(k) <= (1-delta) ||u||_{L^2}^2 / r_k^3`
  for some `delta > 0`, or an equivalent full-pairing estimate with the same
  net margin.

- Why meaningful:
  `[INFERRED]`
  this threshold improves the already-frozen bad term in the same theorem
  ledger after the later bill is repaid; it is not a prettier identity, a
  different architecture, or a gain on a surrogate/local-only piece.

- Weaker thresholds ruled out by sources:
  `[VERIFIED]` constant-mode quotienting is cosmetic because constants are
  already annihilated by the pairing;
  `[VERIFIED]` generic harmonic regularity fails the Tao gate unless it shrinks
  the actual bad coefficient;
  `[VERIFIED]` algebraic rewrites and local geometry fail unless they yield a
  new coefficient estimate on the full pairing;
  `[VERIFIED]` partial improvements that do not lower the actual far-field
  coefficient are screened out by the same-protocol rule.

- Leads worth pursuing:
  test whether the exact pressure-tensor identity can force cancellation of the
  affine-and-higher harmonic moment family strongly enough to imply the same
  full-pairing coefficient shrinkage;
  make any later tensor observable prove net margin on the same estimate rather
  than on a partial surrogate.

- Unexpected findings:
  the old Step-001 far-field packet is substantially more endpoint-concrete
  than the newer tensor branch language;
  the repository already forces constants out of the pairing, so "better modulo
  constants" is dead on arrival;
  no local monotonicity quantity is frozen on disk for this endpoint.

- Computations worth doing later:
  derive an explicit candidate formula for `C_far,eff(k)` under a
  pressure-Hessian or moment-cancellation ansatz;
  test whether any candidate shrinkage survives full harmonic accounting and
  localization losses with positive margin;
  if one survives, push that improved coefficient through the inherited LEI /
  epsilon-regularity contradiction ledger step by step.

